This is consistent with Müllerian agenesis, which can lead to primary amenorrhea. 5-alpha reductase deficiency and Premature ovarian failure do not cause this specific manifestation, while Turner syndrome can cause primary amenorrhea but is usually associated with other physical characteristics.
